HEADWORD: Cosmoplastic
<hw>Cos`mo*plas"tic</hw> <pr>(k?z`m?-pl?s"t?k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>ko`smos</grk> the world + <grk>pla`ssein</grk> to
form.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to a plastic force as operative in the
formation of the world independently of God; world-forming.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Cosmoplastic</xex> and hylozoic atheisms.⟦rdquo⟧
